    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1942-05-19T06:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1942-05-19T06:00:00-05:00" n="12"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d12">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">859A.20/184: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Iceland</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">MacVeagh</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Reykjavik</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-05-19T11:00:00+00:00"
                            >May 19, 1942—11 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received 8:09 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>259. Department’s 136, May 15, 6 p.m. In a communication<note n="10"
                        xml:id="d12fn10">Not printed.</note> which I handed to the Prime
                        Minister<note n="11" xml:id="d12fn11">Olafur Thors was Prime Minister and
                        Minister for Foreign Affairs in the Cabinet formed May 16, 1942.</note>
                    yesterday morning, I informed him that our exchange of notes might be considered
                    as constituting an agreement provided it is understood (1) that no
                    discrimination against the interests of the United States will be rendered
                    possible by the not granting to its nationals and aviation interests at this
                    time of equal treatment with Icelandic nationals and aviation interests; and (2)
                    that ill his stipulation that no future military commitments shall be entered
                    into in connection with the undertakings of the United States military forces
                    here, the word “future” applies only to the period after the war.</p>
                <pb facs="0016" n="10" xml:id="pg_10"/>
                <p>Mr. Thors at once stated verbally afternoon conformed in writing, that the
                    Icelandic Government’s understanding of the above two points conforms with ours
                    as stated, and he has now ordered the issuance of the necessary proclamation
                    establishing the restricted area at Keflavik.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">MacVeagh</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
